===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `man` baraye didane rahnamaye dastoor-haye digar dar terminal estefade mishavad.  
    In dastoor etela'ati dar morede gozine-ha, tarze estefade va karbord-haye har dastoor faraham mikonad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `man [dastoor]`  --> ❓ Rahnamaye dastoor morede nazar ra neshan midahad.
    🔹 `man -k [kalameh kelidi]` --> 🔎 Dastoor-haye marbut be kalameh kelidi ra peyda mikonad.
    🔹 `man -f [dastoor]`  --> 📄 Tafsilati sade dar morede dastoor neshan midahad (hammanند whatis).
    🔹 `man -a [dastoor]` --> 📚 Agar barnameh chand bakhsh rahnama dashteh bashad, hameye anha ra neshan midahad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ man ls

    🔹 Rahnamaye dastoor `ls` ra neshan midahad.

    $ man -k file

    🔹 Dastoor-haye marbut be kalameh "file" ra peyda mikonad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ man pwd

    🔹  Rahnamaye kamel dastoor `pwd` ra neshan midahad, ke tozihat dar morede karbord va gozine-haye an ra dar bar migirad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `man` command is used to display the manual pages for other commands in the terminal.
    It provides information about options, usage, and functionality of each command.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `man [command]` --> ❓ Displays the manual page for the specified command.
    🔹 `man -k [keyword]` --> 🔎 Searches for commands related to the keyword.
    🔹 `man -f [command]` --> 📄 Shows a brief description of the command (similar to whatis).
    🔹 `man -a [command]` --> 📚 If a program has multiple manual sections, shows all of them.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ man ls

    🔹 Displays the manual page for the `ls` command.

    $ man -k file

    🔹 Searches for commands related to the keyword "file".

✅ **Simple Example & Explanation:**

    $ man pwd

    🔹  Displays the complete manual page for the `pwd` command, including explanations of its usage and options.